em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.151em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">∗</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">(</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">s</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">t</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="margin-top: -0.144em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">,</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">a</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></td><td> Exact <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> <strong>or</strong> can recover from overshooting</td><td> Exact <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p> What makes aspiration rescaling harder than Q-learning is that Q-learning does not require Q values to be close to reality to choose the maximizing policy. It only requires that the best action according to <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is the same than the one according to <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^*"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.151em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">∗</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> . In this sense, the learned <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> only needs to be a <i>qualitatively</i> good<i> </i>approximation of <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^*"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.151em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">∗</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> .</p><p> In hard update, if the agent underestimate the return of its action, it might choose maximizing action in the beginning. But if it can recover from it (eg when <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\aleph < 0"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">ℵ</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">&lt;</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">0</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> , it&#39;s able to stop collecting rewards) it might be able to fulfill <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\aleph_0"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">ℵ</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mn" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">0</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> .</p><p> However aspiration rescaling demands values for <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q, \underline Q"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="margin-top: -0.144em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">,</span></span> <span class="mjx-munderover MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-itable" style="margin-bottom: -0.223em;"><span class="mjx-row"><span class="mjx-cell"><span class="mjx-op"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-row"><span class="mjx-under" style="padding-top: 0.12em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style="vertical-align: top;"><span class="mjx-delim-h"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-bottom: 0.537em; padding-top: -0.004em; margin: 0px -0.104em 0px 0px;">–</span> <span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-bottom: 0.537em; padding-top: -0.004em; margin: 0px -0.001em 0px -0.103em;">–</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\overline Q"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-munderover"><span class="mjx-stack"><span class="mjx-over" style="font-size: 70.7%; height: 0.096em; padding-bottom: 0.283em; padding-top: 0.141em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style="vertical-align: top;"><span class="mjx-delim-h"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.301em; padding-bottom: 0.833em; margin: 0px -0.07em 0px -0.069em;">¯</span> <span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.301em; padding-bottom: 0.833em; letter-spacing: -0.252em; margin: 0px 0.036em 0px -0.175em;">¯¯</span> <span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.301em; padding-bottom: 0.833em; margin-right: -0.07em; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 0px;">¯</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-op"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> that are <i>quantitatively</i> good approximations of their true values in order to rescale properly. Another complication arises as the three Q estimators and the policy are interdependent, potentially leading to unstable learning.</p><h2> LRAR-DQN</h2><p> Results on LRAR-DQN confirm our hypothesis that precise Q values are essential for aspiration rescaling. </p><figure class="image"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Z9P2m462wQ4qmH6uo/pfzukkle9mycx1lvesr0" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Z9P2m462wQ4qmH6uo/ki7uqert7x799qctxxxn 127w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Z9P2m462wQ4qmH6uo/kbwryisjuwxeoywyd6ri 207w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Z9P2m462wQ4qmH6uo/njgdwi6bxdedap03u83h 287w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Z9P2m462wQ4qmH6uo/wh1d0yfbkfczuktxxgwk 367w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Z9P2m462wQ4qmH6uo/eeor2pwdc9hoxwe0dr6q 447w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Z9P2m462wQ4qmH6uo/wdkntfamlon7gfze0ral 527w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Z9P2m462wQ4qmH6uo/otstmkvgbvsyjrsqciru 607w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Z9P2m462wQ4qmH6uo/tkl1kpgp9x69fmvkluoa 687w"><figcaption> On each graph, the X-axis is <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\aleph_0"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">ℵ</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mn" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">0</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and Y-axis is<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\mathbb E\ G"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-texatom"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-ams-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">E</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mtext"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="margin-top: -0.291em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">&nbsp;</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">G</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> . The colorscale represents <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\rho"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">ρ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> , from<br> red=0 to green=1</figcaption></figure><p> After 100k steps, in both boat racing and iterated MAB, the two LRA-DQN agents derived from <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^+"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^-"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">−</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> , have already converged to their final policies. However, both Q-estimator still underestimates the Q values. As illustrated in figure <a href="#fig:lrarres">14</a> , waiting for 1M steps does not alter the outcome with hard updates ( <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\rho=0"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">ρ</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.077em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">=</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">0</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> ), which depend less on the exact Q values. Nevertheless, they enable AR ( <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\rho=1"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.519em;">ρ</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.077em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">=</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> ) to match its performance.</p><p> In our experiments, the LRAR-DQN algorithm exhibited suboptimal performance on the empty grid task. A potential explanation, which remains to be empirically validated, is the divergence in state encounters between the <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^+"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^-"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">−</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> during training. Specifically, <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^-"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">−</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> appears to predominantly learn behaviors that lead to prolonged stagnation in the top-left corner, while <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^+"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> seems to be oriented towards reaching the exit within a reasonable timestep. As a future direction, we propose extending the training of both <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^+"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="Q^-"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">Q</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sup" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: 0.513em; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mo" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">−</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> under the guidance of the LRAR-DQN policy to ascertain if this approach rectifies the observed challenges.</p><h1>结论</h1><p>Throughout the duration of this internship, we successfully laid the groundwork for aspiration-based Q-learning and DQN algorithms. These were implemented using Stable Baseline 3 to ensure that, once fully functional, aspiration-based algorithms can be readily assessed across a wide range of environments, notably Atari games. Future work will focus on refining the DQN algorithms, exploring the possibility of deriving aspiration-based algorithms from other RL methodologies such as the Soft Actor-Critic or PPO, and investigating the behavior of <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\aleph"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">ℵ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> -aspiring agent in multi-agent environments both with and without maximizing agents. </p><hr><ol class="footnotes" role="doc-endnotes"><li class="footnote-item" role="doc-endnote" id="fnt7feh5hr6kn"> <span class="footnote-back-link"><sup><strong><a href="#fnreft7feh5hr6kn">^</a></strong></sup></span><div class="footnote-content"><p> Read &quot;aleph&quot;, the first letter of the Hebrew alphabet</p></div></li><li class="footnote-item" role="doc-endnote" id="fnswbxtcnt4ui"> <span class="footnote-back-link"><sup><strong><a href="#fnrefswbxtcnt4ui">^</a></strong></sup></span><div class="footnote-content"><p> In <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="s_1"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span c